snippet.textDisplay: Has anyone noticed the EXTREMELY Bad fitting bonnet?? What a disgrace! Morgan, you should be ashamed. You knew this was going on YouTube yet you coouldn't put a bonnet on the car that FITTED!!! Look at 2:20, and see the (uneven) gap between bonnet and radiator housing. Also, the extremely uneven and unmatching curved gap between the bonnet and the inner wheel arch! What a joke. And at 3:15 one can even see the uneven, and unnecessary, bonnet gap as the car is in motion! And HOW MUCH are these cars?? Some may reply that - Oh, but they're hand made! Well, I would fire the person who thought that that badly fitting bonnet would be OK. Disgracefull. No wonder the British car industry disappeared. No pride in their work - from managent down it would seem. I'm appalled. C'mon Morgan - someone explain that.

snippet.textDisplay: I think that Morgan is the future of sports-car manufacturing:  Ultimately, people aren't going to be looking for ultimate speed, ultimate performance, and especially ultimate technology.  Instead, they are going to be looking for a bespoke car that can deliver what their idea of the "ultimate drive" is.  For some people, it might be a pared down open-top roadster.  For other people, it might be an open-wheeled hot road... or a low-riding cruiser... or a high-performance off-roader... whatever.  The only thing that is for certain is that performance figures will no longer be the primary driving force behind sports-car design or marketing.  Instead, the filling of niche driving interests will.
